benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/paymentMethods/{paymentMethodId}/setDefault - Set the default payment method

covered: Valid Request: Comprehensive coverage of successful updates with required parameters, optional headers, and query parameters (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC14, TC16, TC20, TC24).
Non-Existing Resource: Coverage of 404 paths for missing account, missing payment method, mismatched ownership, and accounts with no payment methods (TC08, TC09, TC10, TC21).
Concurrency: Coverage of race conditions and final default determination (TC22).
Input Security/Validation: Coverage of invalid UUID formats, missing headers, and header-based input validation (TC06, TC07, TC11, TC12, TC19, TC23).
Service Availability/Error Handling: Coverage of 503 and 504 service disruption scenarios (TC13, TC18).
Audit and Observability: Coverage of audit log content when headers and reasons are provided (TC04).
Edge/Boundary & Performance: Coverage of boundary UUIDs (TC16) and performance tests for large numbers of unpaid invoices and high concurrency (TC17, TC22).
Accessibility: Coverage of API documentation and error messages accessibility (TC25).
gaps: Partial Update: No tests for partial updates; PUT semantics may require full updates or explicit allowance for partial payloads.
Internal Server Error: No test for 500 Internal Server Error scenario.
Authorization depth: No test for 403 Forbidden due to insufficient privileges; only 401 Unauthorized is tested.
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
Same-resource concurrency: Concurrency on updating the same resource concurrently is not covered.
Duplicate Submission: No test for idempotency of duplicate submissions.
Edge-case: Additional validation for pluginProperty values beyond max length and empty array edges.
recommendations: Add a test for 403 Forbidden when a user lacks permissions, in addition to 401 Unauthorized.
Add rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system behavior under burst of requests.
Add caching tests to validate ETag and Cache-Control headers.
Add a test for 500 Internal Server Error to cover generic server failures.
Add tests specifically for updating the same resource concurrently to surface race conditions (not just different payment methods).
Add tests for duplicate submissions and idempotency semantics.
Extend pluginProperty validation tests to cover edge cases like duplicates or invalid value types.
